{"lemma":"صَرْدُ","slug":"صَرْدُ","root":"ص.ر.د","root_slug":"ص-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24168","n24172","n24173","n24175"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24168","headword_ar":"صَرِدَ","root":"Srd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaradN","text_ar":"صَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SarodN","text_ar":"صَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saridotu Alyawoma SaradFA $adiydFA","text_ar":"صَرِدْتُ اليَوْمَ صَرَدًا شَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, to day, very cold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very intensely cold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida yawomunaA","text_ar":"صَرِدَ يَوْمُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Our day was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, very cold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very intensely cold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida","text_ar":"صَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, (S, K,) and so the inf. n., (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was quickly sensible of cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida","text_ar":"صَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of milk,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became in a state of decomposition, by reason of cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And, said of a skin, (O, K,) inf. n. as above, (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It emitted its butter in clots:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) of the doing of which it is cured with hot water. (O, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"صَرِدَ عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"page_break","n":1677},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. as above, means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abstained, refrained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desisted, from the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though he became cold with respect to it;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left, relinquished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsook, it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida qalobiY Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"صَرِدَ قَلْبِى عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My heart refrained from the thing; left, relinquished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsook, it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K:) like as one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaHa qalobiY SaridFA","text_ar":"اَصْبَحَ قَلْبِى صَرِدًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the [lizard called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is spoken of as saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laA ya$otahiY A^ano yaridaA \n                      \n                     \n                        A^aSobaHa qalobiY SaridaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My heart has become cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indifferent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposed to abstinence,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not desirous of coming to drink"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida","text_ar":"صَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida Eani Alr~amiy~api","text_ar":"صَرِدَ عَنِ الرَّمِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alr~amiy~api","text_ar":"مِنَ الرَّمِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) said of an arrow, (S, M, A, K,) and of a spear, (M, L,) aor. as above, (L,) and so the inf. n., (M, A, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It passed through,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transpierced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a part of it passed through,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the animal at which it was shot"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrown"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of its sharpness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafa*a Hid~apF","text_ar":"نَفَذَ حِدَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it penetrated so that its extremity passed through;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafa*a Had~uhu","text_ar":"نَفَذَ حَدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarajato $abaApu Had~ihi","text_ar":"خَرَجَتْ شَبَاةُ حَدِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarada","text_ar":"صَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":". (A. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAridN","text_ar":"صَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buqoyaA","text_ar":"بُقْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida","text_ar":"صَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaradN","text_ar":"صَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SarodN","text_ar":"صَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L,) [the latter inf. n. suggesting that one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarada","text_ar":"صَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] said of an arrow, (M, K,) and of a spear and the like, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It missed"},{"kind":"text","text":"the object of aim: thus having two contr. significations: (M, L, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASrd","text_ar":"اصرد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also has the latter of these two significations. (L.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarida","text_ar":"صَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a horse, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaradN","text_ar":"صَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became galled in the place of the saddle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had a white place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white places, on his back, produced by galls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by hair growing in the places of galls:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaridN","text_ar":"صَرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuradN","text_ar":"صُرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] and, said of a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had white fur growing in the place of a gall produced by the saddle, after its healing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO.)       -A4-  See also 4."}],"source_refs":["S","K","O","TA","M","A","L"]},{"entry_id":"n24172","headword_ar":"صَرْدٌ","root":"Srd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaradN","text_ar":"صَرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L,) the former a simple subst. and the latter an inf. n., (Lth,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SariydN","text_ar":"صَرِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coldness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SarodN","text_ar":"صَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a Pers. word, [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarod","text_ar":"سَرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":",] arabicized: (S, K:) or, accord. to a number of authors, it is an Arabic word adopted by the Persians. (MF.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu SarodK","text_ar":"يَوْمُ صَرْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaradK","text_ar":"صَرَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day of cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of intense cold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  For the former, see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaridN","text_ar":"صَرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b3-  Also, the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A high place in mountains;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, L, K;) being the coldest part. (AA, L.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SarodN","text_ar":"صَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pure, unmixed, unadulterated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genuine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, K;) applied to beverage, (L,) such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) and to wine, (L,) and to anything. (M, K.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*ibN SarodN","text_ar":"كَذِبٌ صَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An unmixed lie."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHib~uhu Hub~FA SarodFA","text_ar":"اُحِبُّهُ حُبًّا صَرْدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I love him with a pure, genuine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, love."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayo$N SarodN","text_ar":"جَيْشٌ صَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An army composed only of the sons of one father"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancestor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an army altogether consisting of sons of one's paternal uncle"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one's relations"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AO:) or, (M, A, L, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayo$N SaridN","text_ar":"جَيْشٌ صَرِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaradN","text_ar":"صَرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great army;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an army that appears, from the slowness of its motion, by reason of its great number, to be inanimate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, L.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuradN","text_ar":"صُرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end."}],"source_refs":["S","M","L","K","Lth","TA","AO","A"]},{"entry_id":"n24173","headword_ar":"صَرَدٌ","root":"Srd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SarodN","text_ar":"صَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places:       -A2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuradN","text_ar":"صُرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24175","headword_ar":"صُرَدٌ","root":"Srd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above the size of the sparrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a large head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which preys upon sparrows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bird, black and white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party-coloured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqaEu","text_ar":"اَبْقَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a white belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bird of the crow-kind, also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaAqiY","text_ar":"الوَاقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the Arabs used to regard its cry, (L, Msb,) and the bird itself, (L,) as of evil omen, (L, Msb,) and used to kill it; and they are forbidden to kill it, in order to dispel the idea of a thing's being of evil omen: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there are two species thereof; one species is called by the people of El-'Irák"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaqoEaqu","text_ar":"العَقْعَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a name now applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"magpie, corvus pica"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the other species, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~uradu AlhamohaAmu","text_ar":"الصُّرَدُ الهَمْهَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the L, but in my copy of the Msb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhyAm","text_ar":"الهيام"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the wild sort, which is found in Nejd, upon the trees called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is never seen but upon the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the L, but in my copy of the Msb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is never seen upon the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"springing from tree to tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sukeyn En-Numeyree, L, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when chased, and hard pressed, it is overtaken, and utters a cry like that of the hawk: it preys upon sparrows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) it is described by AHát as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bird black and white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party-coloured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqaEu","text_ar":"اَبْقَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a white belly, and a back of a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDar","text_ar":"اَخْضَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"), [or, as is said in the L,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half white and half black, found in trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large in the head and beak, having a talon with which it preys upon sparrows and other small birds, as large as the point of a spear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) some add to this that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almujaw~afu","text_ar":"المُجَوَّفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because of the whiteness of its belly; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axoTabu","text_ar":"الاَخْطَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because of the dark, or ashy, dust-colour of its back; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axoyalu","text_ar":"الاَخْيَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a name now applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green woodpecker, picus viridis"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because of its diversity of colour; that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is never seen but upon a branch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY $uEobapK","text_ar":"فِى شُعْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so in the L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or a tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and can scarcely ever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"never, be taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"can never be taken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is regarded as of evil omen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) Sgh says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumayoTN","text_ar":"سُمَيْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [perhaps a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$umayoTN","text_ar":"شُمَيْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because black and white,] in the dim. form: (Msb:) [it is said that] it was the first bird that fasted for the sake of God: (K:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SirodaAnN","text_ar":"صِرْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, Msb, K:) and the female is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuradapN","text_ar":"صُرَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A white place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produced by galls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the saddle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuradapN","text_ar":"صُرَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a white place produced by hair growing in the place of a gall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"likened to the colour of the bird thus called: (A:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SirodaAnN","text_ar":"صِرْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, A.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A white place on the hump of a camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white fur growing in the place of a gall produced by the saddle, after its healing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO:) pl. as above."},{"kind":"page_break","n":1678},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, M.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain vein"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the tongue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the lower part of the tongue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) of the horse. (As, M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~uradaAni","text_ar":"الصُّرَدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two veins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Ks, S, M, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaraAni","text_ar":"اَخْضَرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Lth, Ks, M, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the lower part of the tongue, by means of which the tongue moves about,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Ks, L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"penetrating within"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasotaboTinaAni","text_ar":"يَسْتَبْطِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two veins, on the right and left of the tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two bones, which erect"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuqiymaAni","text_ar":"يُقِيمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) Yezeed Ibn-Es- Sa'ik in his saying"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lahu SuradaAni munoTaliqaA All~isaAni"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribaAni","text_ar":"ذَرِبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribaA All~isaAni","text_ar":"ذَرِبَا اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aribN lisaAnuhumaA","text_ar":"ذَرِبٌ لِسَانُهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu lisaAnN *aribN","text_ar":"لَهُ لِسَانٌ ذَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unbridled, tongue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the phrase that he uses being pleonastic]. (S.) ―         -b4-  Also, (M, L,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SarodN","text_ar":"صَرْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaradN","text_ar":"صَرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the more known, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A nail in a spear-head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of which the shaft is fastened to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K. *) ―         -b5-  Accord. to Sh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fat~aHa Suradahu","text_ar":"فَتَّحَ صُرَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened his mind, so as to reveal his secrets."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [But this is perhaps a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ftH","text_ar":"فتح"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Surarahu","text_ar":"صُرَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sur~apN","text_ar":"صُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","T","A","Msb","L","Mgh","AO","As","Lth","Ks","TA"]}]}}